{
  "stem": "25348.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there was-- the Jewish girls always sat separately, were divided by benches from the Catholic girls.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we had to get up to the Catholic prayer every morning, of course.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We knew it by heart, which [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at the-- from what flows from the interview later on stood me by good stead, in good stead because it identified me as a Catholic.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because there's only one word for it-- anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was prevalent at schools, though perhaps it didn't go-- it wasn't an order [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] from the top.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was prevalent in higher institutions because there was numerous classes in Lwow where students were not-- there was a very limited number of Jewish students permitted to study.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that explains my brother's absence from Poland during his years of study, that he had to go to France.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was just quite natural for us to accept it, that we were divided by several benches from the Catholic girls.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Though I must say that at primary school and then at medium school-- because I went to school there until the age of 13-- there was no hostility amongst us.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there were some schools, I believe, that there was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Outside the school?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't experience it personally, but I had-- I could observe it everywhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- for example, there was a Jewish shop not far from us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a butcher shop.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at that time-- in my times, butcher shops were divided, to an extent, and they were selling also-- they were also selling fish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Jewish consumers of fish were mostly Friday customers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, they used to buy fish for Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
